<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-02T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="875" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/991a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Chase</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-02T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                        1920—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>16. The President has issued instructions to recognize the present
                            Government of Costa Rica. You are therefore directed to communicate this
                            fact to the Minister for Foreign Affairs and to be governed
                            accordingly.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>